1
00:02:28,858 --> 00:02:31,068
I hear they might promote Bryukhanov.

2
00:02:32,236 --> 00:02:35,406
This little problem we have
with the safety test,

3
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:38,742
if it's completed successfully...

4
00:02:40,077 --> 00:02:42,830
Yes, I think promotion's very likely.

5
00:02:43,873 --> 00:02:45,875
Who knows, maybe Moscow.

6
00:02:47,877 --> 00:02:50,254
Naturally, they'll put me in charge
once he's gone,

7
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:53,090
and then I'll need someone
to take my old job.

8
00:02:55,050 --> 00:02:57,136
I could pick SITNIKOV.

9
00:03:05,978 --> 00:03:07,771
I would like to be considered.

10
00:03:11,317 --> 00:03:12,693
We'll keep that in mind.

11
00:03:14,612 --> 00:03:18,741
Viktor PETROVICH, preparations
for the test have gone smoothly.

12
00:03:18,824 --> 00:03:22,119
Comrade Dyatlov's been working
per my instructions,

13
00:03:22,203 --> 00:03:25,664
and Reactor 4 output's been
reduced to 1,600 megawatts.

14
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:29,835
With your approval, we're ready
to continue lowering power to...

15
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:31,086
<i>We have o wail.</i>

16
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:33,756
Is, uh...

17
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:36,800
Are you going to ask me
if there's a problem, Nikolai?

18
00:03:37,259 --> 00:03:39,094
You can't read a fucking face?

19
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:42,056
Three years,
I've tried to finish this test.

20
00:03:42,139 --> 00:03:43,265
Three years.

21
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:52,942
I've just had a call from
the grid controller in Kiev.

22
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:55,194
He says we can't
lower power any further,

23
00:03:55,277 --> 00:03:56,570
not for another 10 hours.

24
00:03:56,654 --> 00:03:58,489
A grid controller?
Where does he get off...

25
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:01,200
It's not the grid controller's
decision, Dyatlov.

26
00:04:02,368 --> 00:04:03,702
It's the end of the month.

27
00:04:04,495 --> 00:04:07,248
All the productivity quotas.

28
00:04:07,331 --> 00:04:10,042
Everyone's working overtime.
The factories need power.

29
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,877
Someone's pushing down from above.

30
00:04:11,961 --> 00:04:13,504
Not that we'll never know who.

31
00:04:14,797 --> 00:04:16,131
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

32
00:04:22,179 --> 00:04:24,431
So, do we have to scrap it or what?

33
00:04:24,515 --> 00:04:26,308
No, I don't think so.

34
00:04:26,976 --> 00:04:29,561
If we need to wait 10 hours, we wait.

35
00:04:29,645 --> 00:04:33,065
Running at half power, we're not
going to have stability issues?

36
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:35,776
-No, I should think...
-I'm not asking you.

37
00:04:38,904 --> 00:04:40,155
DYATLOV: It's safe.

38
00:04:40,614 --> 00:04:42,032
We'll maintain at 1,600.

39
00:04:42,116 --> 00:04:44,535
I'll go home, get some sleep,
come back tonight.

40
00:04:44,618 --> 00:04:45,869
We'll proceed then.

41
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:48,831
I'll personally supervise the test.

42
00:04:49,581 --> 00:04:51,375
And it will be completed.

43
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:56,714
Well, I'm not waiting around, then.

44
00:04:58,048 --> 00:04:59,383
Call me when it's done.

45
00:06:36,980 --> 00:06:38,065
How do you feel?

46
00:06:40,442 --> 00:06:43,028
You went to the doctor yesterday.
How is your health?

47
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:45,239
You don't know?

48
00:06:47,449 --> 00:06:48,784
CHARKOV: From Vienna.

49
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:50,494
Do you read German?

50
00:06:52,287 --> 00:06:57,126
It says, "At last a Soviet
scientist who tells the truth."

51
00:06:57,793 --> 00:06:59,795
Obviously, I resent the insinuation,

52
00:06:59,878 --> 00:07:01,004
but I think it's fair to say

53
00:07:01,088 --> 00:07:03,382
you made an excellent impression
at the conference.

54
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:05,884
Turns out, you're quite good at this.

55
00:07:06,427 --> 00:07:08,345
At what? Lying?

56
00:07:08,429 --> 00:07:11,390
Statecraft, Legasov. Statecraft.

57
00:07:11,515 --> 00:07:14,059
The West is now satisfied

58
00:07:14,143 --> 00:07:16,979
that Chernobyl was solely
the result of operator error,

59
00:07:17,062 --> 00:07:18,480
which it essentially was.

60
00:07:19,273 --> 00:07:20,983
We have you to thank for that,

61
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:22,526
and we intend to.

62
00:07:26,864 --> 00:07:28,907
"Hero of the Soviet Union."

63
00:07:29,366 --> 00:07:31,118
Our highest honor.

64
00:07:31,493 --> 00:07:33,871
They haven't even given it to me.

65
00:07:34,455 --> 00:07:37,666
"Promotion to director
of the Kurchatov Institute."

66
00:07:41,086 --> 00:07:42,421
I'm humbled.

67
00:07:43,046 --> 00:07:47,050
I don't think there's anything humble
about you, Valery Alexeyevich.

68
00:07:47,134 --> 00:07:49,011
These rewards are not yours yet.

69
00:07:49,678 --> 00:07:51,472
First, your testimony at the trial.

70
00:07:51,555 --> 00:07:55,476
Comrade Charkov,
I understand my duty to the State.

71
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:58,729
But you gave us assurances.

72
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:01,982
The reactors would be made safe.

73
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:04,526
It's been months.
No changes have been made.

74
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:07,946
-No changes even discussed.
-First, the trial.

75
00:08:09,448 --> 00:08:11,742
Once it's over,
we will have our villains,

76
00:08:11,825 --> 00:08:14,995
we will have our hero,
we will have our truth.

77
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:18,957
After that,
we can deal with the reactors.

78
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:29,319
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

79
00:09:30,362 --> 00:09:31,863
(SIGHS)

80
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:45,252
Did you take a train?

81
00:09:45,877 --> 00:09:47,838
Yes, I took a train.

82
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,591
Now let's talk about Vienna.

83
00:09:51,675 --> 00:09:53,302
I'm not here to scold you.

84
00:09:53,969 --> 00:09:57,306
I know how the world works
despite what Shcherbina says.

85
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,518
So, why are you here?

86
00:10:02,728 --> 00:10:04,521
Because I'm brutally stubborn.

87
00:10:05,147 --> 00:10:06,898
Which you were hoping for.

88
00:10:11,361 --> 00:10:15,115
Charkov is saying they're going to fix
the reactors after the trial.

89
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:19,286
-Do you believe him?
-(SNICKERS)

90
00:10:21,830 --> 00:10:23,999
The State will never
willingly fix the reactors

91
00:10:24,082 --> 00:10:27,419
because acknowledging the problem
means admitting that they lied.

92
00:10:27,502 --> 00:10:29,212
They will have to be forced.

93
00:10:36,511 --> 00:10:39,640
At the trial,
you're going to tell the truth.

94
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,685
You're going to convince the jury.

95
00:10:43,769 --> 00:10:45,437
It's a show trial.

96
00:10:46,313 --> 00:10:48,106
The jury's already been
handed their verdict.

97
00:10:48,190 --> 00:10:49,524
I'm not talking about them.

98
00:10:51,902 --> 00:10:55,781
The Central Committee have invited
members of the scientific community

99
00:10:55,864 --> 00:10:57,282
to observe the trial.

100
00:10:57,824 --> 00:11:00,702
Our colleagues, from Kurchatov,

101
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:03,205
from Sredmash, from Minenergo,

102
00:11:03,288 --> 00:11:06,875
they will be sitting in the crowd
listening to every word you say.

103
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:09,169
A jury that only we know is there.

104
00:11:09,252 --> 00:11:12,756
And when your testimony arrives
at the moment of the explosion?

105
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:17,844
That is when our jury
will finally hear the truth.

106
00:11:18,512 --> 00:11:21,556
-And do what with it?
-Insist on reform.

107
00:11:23,100 --> 00:11:25,477
Not just to the RBMK,
but the entire industry.

108
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:26,561
No, no, no.

109
00:11:26,645 --> 00:11:28,146
-They can't function without us.
-No, no, no.

110
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,231
If we...

111
00:11:29,314 --> 00:11:33,360
Do you know what happened to Volkov,
the man whose report you found?

112
00:11:34,069 --> 00:11:37,823
They just removed him
from his position at the Institute.

113
00:11:38,740 --> 00:11:41,034
Sacked for the crime of knowing.

114
00:11:42,035 --> 00:11:47,040
And you think that these scientists,
handpicked to witness a show trial,

115
00:11:47,124 --> 00:11:50,335
will somehow be stirred
into action by me?

116
00:11:51,128 --> 00:11:54,631
Because of some heroic stance
I take in defiance of the State?

117
00:11:54,715 --> 00:11:55,966
Yes.

118
00:11:56,049 --> 00:11:57,092
Why?

119
00:11:57,175 --> 00:12:00,595
Because you're Valery Legasov,
and you mean something.

120
00:12:02,764 --> 00:12:05,434
I'd like to think that if I spoke out,
it would be enough.

121
00:12:06,727 --> 00:12:08,562
But I know how the world works.

122
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:14,609
They will shoot me, Khomyuk.

123
00:12:18,155 --> 00:12:21,324
You told me to find out what happened.

124
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:23,535
I spoke to dozens of people.

125
00:12:23,618 --> 00:12:26,830
Every word they said, I wrote down.

126
00:12:28,081 --> 00:12:29,416
All in these books.

127
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:32,335
These are the ones
who are still alive.

128
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:34,045
These are the ones who are dead.

129
00:12:34,129 --> 00:12:35,756
They died rescuing each other.

130
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,092
Putting out fires,
tending to the wounded.

131
00:12:39,176 --> 00:12:40,927
They didn't hesitate.
They didn't waiver.

132
00:12:41,011 --> 00:12:43,096
They simply did what had to be done.

133
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:44,181
So have I

134
00:12:45,474 --> 00:12:46,475
So have I

135
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:49,644
I went willingly to an open reactor.

136
00:12:50,479 --> 00:12:52,981
So I've already given my life.

137
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:55,525
Isn't that enough?

138
00:12:57,486 --> 00:12:59,821
No, I'm sorry, but it is not.

139
00:14:09,307 --> 00:14:12,185
"The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of the Soviet Union

140
00:14:12,269 --> 00:14:15,230
and the Presidium of the
Supreme Soviet of the U.S.S.R.

141
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:18,608
has determined that justice
be carried out on behalf of the People

142
00:14:18,692 --> 00:14:21,319
in accordance with the
general goal of our Party

143
00:14:21,403 --> 00:14:24,990
as determined by its 20th,
21st and 22nd Congresses,

144
00:14:25,073 --> 00:14:26,992
which is a Leninist goal.

145
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:31,037
It was, is, and will be the only
immutable goal in the Soviet state.

146
00:14:31,121 --> 00:14:32,539
The path of Leninist principles

147
00:14:32,622 --> 00:14:35,292
shall be consistently
and undeviatingly followed,

148
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:38,211
as it expresses the vital
interests of the Soviet people,

149
00:14:38,587 --> 00:14:39,921
its hopes and aspirations

150
00:14:40,005 --> 00:14:42,173
as we guide the life of
the Party and the State.

151
00:14:42,424 --> 00:14:44,467
This session of court is now open,

152
00:14:44,551 --> 00:14:47,387
Comrade Judge
Milan Kadnikov presiding."

153
00:14:49,014 --> 00:14:50,223
Indictments.

154
00:14:50,307 --> 00:14:52,350
Viktor Bryukhanov,

155
00:14:52,434 --> 00:14:54,644
Anatoly Dyatlov,

156
00:14:54,728 --> 00:14:56,771
Nikolai Fomin,

157
00:14:56,855 --> 00:14:59,858
are accused of violating
Article 220 Section 2

158
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:02,027
of the Criminal Code
of the Soviet Union,

159
00:15:02,110 --> 00:15:06,072
resulting in a nuclear disaster
on April 26, 1986.

160
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:09,618
<i>The State calls witnesses
Comrade Khomyuk</i>

161
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:12,120
of the Byelorussian Nuclear Institute,

162
00:15:12,203 --> 00:15:16,207
Comrade Legasov of the Kurchatov
Institute of Atomic Energy,

163
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,295
and Comrade Boris
Evdokimovich Shcherbina,

164
00:15:20,962 --> 00:15:23,465
Deputy Chairman of
the Council of Ministers

165
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:26,343
and head of the Bureau
for Fuel and Energy.

166
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:47,906
(DOOR CLOSES)

167
00:16:01,169 --> 00:16:05,382
It began with,
of all things, a safety test.

168
00:16:06,591 --> 00:16:09,344
Why was there need
for a safety test at all?

169
00:16:10,053 --> 00:16:13,223
Reactor number 4 was not new
when the accident occurred.

170
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:18,645
In fact, it went into operation
on December 20th, 1983.

171
00:16:19,562 --> 00:16:22,691
Eleven days later,
on the last day of the year,

172
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:28,029
plant director Viktor Bryukhanov
signed this document,

173
00:16:29,447 --> 00:16:34,452
certifying the completion
of the construction of the reactor.

174
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:39,499
As a result of finishing the work
before the end of the year,

175
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:44,629
Comrade Bryukhanov was awarded
Hero of Socialist Labor.

176
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:49,092
Comrade Fomin was awarded
for Valorous Labor.

177
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:53,555
Comrade Dyatlov was given
an Order of the Red Banner.

178
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:58,435
But their work was not finished.

179
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:03,356
And this document was a lie.

180
00:17:04,983 --> 00:17:07,318
In order to sign this certificate,

181
00:17:07,569 --> 00:17:11,781
all safety tests had to have
been successfully completed,

182
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:13,658
and yet, one remained.

183
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:21,332
A nuclear reactor generates
heat in the core here.

184
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:24,544
A series of pumps, here and here,

185
00:17:24,627 --> 00:17:27,672
send a constant flow of cooling water
through the core.

186
00:17:28,173 --> 00:17:30,675
The core's heat
turns the water to steam,

187
00:17:30,759 --> 00:17:33,053
and the steam spins the turbine here,

188
00:17:33,136 --> 00:17:34,763
and the result is electricity.

189
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:38,391
But what if a power plant
has no power?

190
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:43,021
What if the power feeding
the plant itself is disrupted?

191
00:17:43,813 --> 00:17:48,193
A blackout, equipment failure,
or an attack by a foreign enemy?

192
00:17:49,277 --> 00:17:51,154
If there's no power,

193
00:17:51,237 --> 00:17:53,990
the pumps cannot move
water through the core.

194
00:17:54,407 --> 00:17:56,826
And without water, the core overheats,

195
00:17:56,910 --> 00:17:58,453
the fuel melts down.

196
00:17:58,536 --> 00:18:01,039
In short, a nuclear disaster.

197
00:18:01,122 --> 00:18:02,248
The solution?

198
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:06,169
Three diesel fuel
backup generators here.

199
00:18:06,753 --> 00:18:08,546
So, problem solved?

200
00:18:08,922 --> 00:18:10,298
No.

201
00:18:10,882 --> 00:18:13,426
Bryukhanov knew that the problem
was not solved at all.

202
00:18:13,968 --> 00:18:16,888
The backup generators took
approximately one minute

203
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:19,349
to reach the speed required

204
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:21,643
to power the pumps
and prevent a meltdown,

205
00:18:21,726 --> 00:18:24,729
and by that time,
it would be too late.

206
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:28,024
So we arrive at the safety test.

207
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:31,611
The theory was this,

208
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:33,905
if the facility lost power,

209
00:18:33,988 --> 00:18:35,865
the turbine, which had been spinning,

210
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:38,827
would take some time
to slow down and stop.

211
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:42,705
What if you could take the electricity
it was still generating

212
00:18:42,789 --> 00:18:44,249
and transfer it to the pumps?

213
00:18:44,332 --> 00:18:48,169
What if the dying turbine could keep
the pumps working long enough

214
00:18:48,253 --> 00:18:52,340
to bridge the 60-second gap
until the generators came on?

215
00:18:53,341 --> 00:18:54,551
(COUGHS)

216
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:57,428
(COUGHS)

217
00:18:57,512 --> 00:18:58,847
Any questions?

218
00:19:00,431 --> 00:19:03,643
No. Continue, please.

219
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:07,814
To test this theory,

220
00:19:07,897 --> 00:19:12,318
the reactor is placed in a reduced
power mode, 700 megawatts,

221
00:19:12,402 --> 00:19:14,154
to simulate a blackout condition.

222
00:19:15,238 --> 00:19:17,157
Then the turbines are turned off,

223
00:19:17,407 --> 00:19:19,200
and as they slowly spin down,

224
00:19:19,284 --> 00:19:21,119
their electrical output is measured

225
00:19:21,202 --> 00:19:24,164
to see if it's enough
to power the pumps.

226
00:19:24,831 --> 00:19:26,332
The science is strong,

227
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:32,088
but a test is only as good
as the men carrying it out.

228
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:36,426
Now, the first time they tried,
they failed.

229
00:19:37,135 --> 00:19:39,429
The second time they tried,
they failed.

230
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:42,223
The third time they tried,
they failed.

231
00:19:42,932 --> 00:19:45,643
The fourth time they tried

232
00:19:45,727 --> 00:19:49,355
was April 26th, 1986.

233
00:20:01,534 --> 00:20:03,244
STEPASHIN: Comrade Khomyuk.

234
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:11,836
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

235
00:20:13,922 --> 00:20:16,132
(LOW INDISTINCT CHATTER)

236
00:20:27,352 --> 00:20:29,103
To understand
what happened that night,

237
00:20:29,187 --> 00:20:31,231
we have to go back 10 hours earlier,

238
00:20:31,314 --> 00:20:34,692
April 25th, the day the test
was meant to take place.

239
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:38,238
By 2:00 in the afternoon,
the reactor has been lowered by half

240
00:20:38,321 --> 00:20:41,449
from its normal output level
of 3,200 megawatts

241
00:20:41,532 --> 00:20:43,785
to 1,600 megawatts and is stable

242
00:20:43,868 --> 00:20:46,788
and ready to be reduced to its
final output level for the test,

243
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:48,414
700 megawatts.

244
00:20:49,082 --> 00:20:52,710
But before they can proceed,
there is a phone call.

245
00:20:54,128 --> 00:20:57,131
Power grid officials in Kiev
say that they cannot afford

246
00:20:57,215 --> 00:21:00,510
a further reduction in the electricity
until after midnight.

247
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:02,929
They are asking for a 10-hour delay.

248
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:06,057
This is the first critical moment,

249
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:08,768
the first link
in the chain of disaster.

250
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:12,230
Competent management would have
insisted on canceling the test.

251
00:21:13,439 --> 00:21:16,192
These three men allowed it to proceed.

252
00:21:18,111 --> 00:21:20,029
Why was this delay so dangerous?

253
00:21:20,363 --> 00:21:22,282
It created two problems.

254
00:21:22,949 --> 00:21:25,118
One of them is scientific in nature,

255
00:21:26,828 --> 00:21:28,496
and the other is very human.

256
00:21:29,747 --> 00:21:31,582
This is the one
we will consider first.

257
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:36,587
At midnight, there is a shift change.

258
00:21:50,101 --> 00:21:51,102
Hey.

259
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:54,522
-Khodemchuk...
-Forget it. Find another fool.

260
00:21:55,273 --> 00:21:57,567
Toptunov, want to buy a motorcycle?

261
00:21:57,650 --> 00:22:00,028
BRAZHNIK: Toptunov?
He's just a little boy.

262
00:22:00,111 --> 00:22:01,988
He's got more hair on his face
than on his balls.

263
00:22:02,071 --> 00:22:04,324
Hair? Is that what's on his lip?

264
00:22:04,407 --> 00:22:06,326
(MEN CHUCKLING)

265
00:22:06,409 --> 00:22:07,493
Leonid Fedorovych.

266
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:10,705
Akimov says to come to the
control room as soon as you can.

267
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:12,415
-Is he already here?
-He came in early.

268
00:22:12,957 --> 00:22:14,208
Something about a test.

269
00:22:16,044 --> 00:22:18,254
You see? Desperate.

270
00:22:20,256 --> 00:22:21,424
(DOOR OPENS)

271
00:22:24,635 --> 00:22:26,012
(DOOR CLOSES)

272
00:22:27,889 --> 00:22:29,057
TOPTUNOV: Sasha?

273
00:22:30,725 --> 00:22:33,102
You know the test
they were supposed to run?

274
00:22:34,145 --> 00:22:36,814
The turbine rundown,
they tried it last year.

275
00:22:36,898 --> 00:22:40,068
They couldn't do it on the day shift,
so they've given it to us.

276
00:22:40,151 --> 00:22:41,319
To us?

277
00:22:41,402 --> 00:22:42,779
-We don't know what...
-AKIMOV: Shh...

278
00:22:44,697 --> 00:22:46,699
-We don't know what it is.
-It's fine.

279
00:22:46,783 --> 00:22:48,910
We take it down to 700, hold it there,

280
00:22:48,993 --> 00:22:51,412
the rest is Stolyarchuk
and Kirschenbaum, but...

281
00:22:51,746 --> 00:22:54,082
Dyatlov is gonna be supervising.

282
00:22:54,791 --> 00:22:56,626
I have to do something
I've never done before

283
00:22:56,709 --> 00:22:58,044
with Dyatlov looking over my shoulder?

284
00:22:58,127 --> 00:23:00,963
Yeah, well, don't worry,
we'll do it together.

285
00:23:01,047 --> 00:23:02,590
I'm just looking
at the instructions now.

286
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,177
Are we supposed to do those or not?

287
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:17,105
<i>Yes, this is Akimov in 4.</i>

288
00:23:18,272 --> 00:23:21,234
I have the manual
for the rundown test.

289
00:23:21,901 --> 00:23:23,694
You did it last year.

290
00:23:24,487 --> 00:23:26,864
Yes, in the program,
there's instructions of what to do,

291
00:23:26,948 --> 00:23:29,242
and then, well,
there's a lot of things crossed out.

292
00:23:29,325 --> 00:23:30,326
What should I...

293
00:23:32,453 --> 00:23:33,579
Well, what should I...

294
00:23:36,082 --> 00:23:37,125
Are you sure?

295
00:23:38,626 --> 00:23:40,461
Right. Thank you.

296
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:44,382
He says to follow
the crossed-out instructions.

297
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:46,509
So then why are they crossed out?

298
00:23:47,260 --> 00:23:48,469
(DOOR OPENS)

299
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:55,226
We've been cleared to run the test.

300
00:23:56,227 --> 00:23:57,812
1,600. Good.

301
00:23:58,688 --> 00:24:01,315
Now, is it too much to ask that
you all know what you're doing?

302
00:24:01,399 --> 00:24:03,234
-Well...
-Yes. Absolutely.

303
00:24:04,819 --> 00:24:06,279
-Stolyarchuk?
-Yes.

304
00:24:06,362 --> 00:24:09,365
-Kirschenbaum?
-Uh, I haven't reviewed.

305
00:24:09,449 --> 00:24:11,242
We only just found out really...

306
00:24:11,325 --> 00:24:12,535
There, review it.

307
00:24:12,618 --> 00:24:14,704
Or you can just do what I tell you.

308
00:24:14,787 --> 00:24:17,415
I think even you, stupid as you are,
can manage that.

309
00:24:18,583 --> 00:24:19,584
Well, let's go.

310
00:24:23,546 --> 00:24:26,466
I'm supposed to switch the turbine off
while the reactor's still running?

311
00:24:26,549 --> 00:24:29,969
-This is not good...
-Shut the fuck up and do your job!

312
00:24:31,053 --> 00:24:34,474
Toptunov, reduce power to 700.

313
00:24:36,309 --> 00:24:38,352
(WHISPERS) I've never done this
with the power so low before.

314
00:24:38,436 --> 00:24:39,812
(WHISPERS) It's okay. I'm with you.

315
00:24:45,651 --> 00:24:47,195
Reducing power to 700.

316
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:51,073
KHOMYUK: I want you
to think of Yuri Gagarin.

317
00:24:53,242 --> 00:24:55,870
I want you to imagine
that he has been told nothing

318
00:24:55,953 --> 00:24:57,205
of his mission into space

319
00:24:57,288 --> 00:24:59,457
until the moment
that he is on the launch pad.

320
00:24:59,749 --> 00:25:01,792
I want you to imagine that all he has

321
00:25:01,876 --> 00:25:04,462
is a list of instructions
that he has never seen before,

322
00:25:04,545 --> 00:25:06,589
some of which have been crossed out.

323
00:25:07,089 --> 00:25:10,843
This is exactly what was happening
in the control room of Reactor 4.

324
00:25:11,594 --> 00:25:14,222
The night shift had not been trained
to perform the experiment.

325
00:25:14,305 --> 00:25:16,891
They hadn't even been
warned it was happening.

326
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:18,893
Leonid Toptunov,

327
00:25:18,976 --> 00:25:21,562
the operator
responsible for controlling

328
00:25:21,646 --> 00:25:24,106
and stabilizing the reactor
that night was

329
00:25:25,566 --> 00:25:27,527
all of 25 years old.

330
00:25:28,986 --> 00:25:30,863
And his total experience on the job?

331
00:25:32,114 --> 00:25:33,199
Four months.

332
00:25:35,076 --> 00:25:37,703
This is the human problem
created by the delay.

333
00:25:38,829 --> 00:25:41,707
But inside the reactor core,

334
00:25:41,791 --> 00:25:43,918
in the space
between the atoms themselves,

335
00:25:44,418 --> 00:25:47,088
something far more dangerous
is forming.

336
00:25:47,171 --> 00:25:48,589
A poison.

337
00:25:50,383 --> 00:25:52,176
The time is 28 past midnight.

338
00:26:10,987 --> 00:26:12,572
Comrade Legasov.

339
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:35,261
(TROLLEY RUMBLING)

340
00:26:50,234 --> 00:26:52,653
I'm pleased to see some
of my colleagues here

341
00:26:52,737 --> 00:26:55,406
from the Kurchatov Institute
and Minenergo.

342
00:26:56,866 --> 00:26:58,909
(CLEARS THROAT) But you don't
need to be a nuclear scientist

343
00:26:58,993 --> 00:27:00,995
to understand what
happened at Chernobyl.

344
00:27:02,038 --> 00:27:04,123
You only need to know this.

345
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:08,878
There are essentially two things
that happen inside a nuclear reactor.

346
00:27:09,545 --> 00:27:15,343
The reactivity, which generates power,
either goes up or it goes down.

347
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:17,011
That's it.

348
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:20,723
All the operators do
IS maintain balance.

349
00:27:23,726 --> 00:27:24,894
Uranium fuel.

350
00:27:27,521 --> 00:27:32,234
As uranium atoms split apart
and collide, reactivity goes up.

351
00:27:32,318 --> 00:27:34,278
But if you don't balance
the reactivity,

352
00:27:34,362 --> 00:27:36,364
it never stops rising. So...

353
00:27:38,616 --> 00:27:41,035
Boron control rods.

354
00:27:41,118 --> 00:27:45,790
They reduce reactivity
like brakes on a car.

355
00:27:47,291 --> 00:27:51,003
But there's a third factor
to consider, water.

356
00:27:52,672 --> 00:27:55,216
Cool water takes heat
out of the system.

357
00:27:55,299 --> 00:27:58,636
As it does, it turns to steam,
or what we call a "void."

358
00:27:58,719 --> 00:28:02,139
In an RBMK reactor
of the type used at Chernobyl,

359
00:28:02,223 --> 00:28:06,060
there's something called
a "positive void coefficient."

360
00:28:06,143 --> 00:28:07,311
What does that mean?

361
00:28:08,187 --> 00:28:12,525
It means that the more steam
present within the system,

362
00:28:12,608 --> 00:28:14,694
the higher the reactivity,

363
00:28:14,777 --> 00:28:17,697
which means more heat,
which means more steam,

364
00:28:17,780 --> 00:28:18,781
which means...

365
00:28:19,740 --> 00:28:23,119
It would appear we have
a vicious cycle on our hands.

366
00:28:23,494 --> 00:28:26,247
And we would, were it not for this...

367
00:28:32,378 --> 00:28:37,758
And we would, were it not for this,

368
00:28:37,842 --> 00:28:40,136
the negative temperature coefficient.

369
00:28:41,470 --> 00:28:47,143
When nuclear fuel gets hotter,
it gets less reactive,

370
00:28:48,436 --> 00:28:50,354
so fuel increases reactivity.

371
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,941
Control rods and water reduce it.

372
00:28:54,024 --> 00:28:56,402
Steam increases it,

373
00:28:56,485 --> 00:28:58,946
and the rise in temperature
reduces it.

374
00:29:00,698 --> 00:29:03,534
This is the invisible dance

375
00:29:03,617 --> 00:29:07,288
that powers entire cities
without smoke or flame.

376
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:09,707
And it is beautiful,

377
00:29:10,791 --> 00:29:12,293
when things are normal.

378
00:29:14,128 --> 00:29:17,047
As uranium splits apart
to release energy,

379
00:29:17,131 --> 00:29:20,551
it breaks down
into a new element, xenon.

380
00:29:20,634 --> 00:29:23,554
Xenon reduces reactivity.

381
00:29:23,637 --> 00:29:26,182
This is the poison
Comrade Khomyuk mentioned.

382
00:29:27,141 --> 00:29:29,185
When the core
is running at full power,

383
00:29:29,268 --> 00:29:32,146
it burns the xenon away
before it can cause a problem.

384
00:29:32,229 --> 00:29:34,440
But because of the delay,

385
00:29:34,523 --> 00:29:39,361
Chernobyl Reactor 4 has been held
at half power for 10 hours.

386
00:29:40,070 --> 00:29:42,323
The xenon did not burn away.

387
00:29:44,158 --> 00:29:47,119
It built up, poisoning the core.

388
00:29:48,579 --> 00:29:50,331
We're starting to lose balance.

389
00:29:50,414 --> 00:29:54,210
-(COUGHING)
-LEGASOV: At 28 minutes past midnight,

390
00:29:54,293 --> 00:29:57,296
the reactor is now primed
to slow down.

391
00:29:58,130 --> 00:30:01,342
And yet, in less than an hour,
it will explode.

392
00:30:02,384 --> 00:30:05,471
If you can't understand
how a stalled nuclear reactor

393
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:08,265
could lead to an explosion,
I don't blame you.

394
00:30:08,349 --> 00:30:12,102
After all, you don't work in the
control room of a nuclear power plant.

395
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:15,397
But as it turned out,

396
00:30:15,481 --> 00:30:19,485
the men who did
didn't understand it either.

397
00:30:25,866 --> 00:30:26,909
Easy now.

398
00:30:27,409 --> 00:30:28,536
Take it down.

399
00:30:29,453 --> 00:30:31,664
Good. Like that.

400
00:30:31,747 --> 00:30:33,249
DYATLOV: You should have
finished by now.

401
00:30:33,332 --> 00:30:35,292
We're following protocol
for reduction rate.

402
00:30:35,376 --> 00:30:37,211
You're procrastinating.

403
00:30:37,294 --> 00:30:39,755
There are 10 other men in this plant
who would've done it already.

404
00:30:39,839 --> 00:30:42,174
(WHISPERS) Keep working.
You're doing fine.

405
00:30:51,684 --> 00:30:55,062
Kirschenbaum, come get me
when these old women are ready.

406
00:30:55,145 --> 00:30:56,438
Yes, Comrade Dyatlov.

407
00:31:04,822 --> 00:31:06,198
(DOOR CLOSES)

408
00:31:15,875 --> 00:31:20,296
Okay, very slow now.
Let's ease it down to 700.

409
00:31:23,632 --> 00:31:26,969
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, slow.
- I didn't move any rods there.

410
00:31:36,562 --> 00:31:39,982
-What is this?
-I'm not even touching it.

411
00:32:05,007 --> 00:32:06,133
We did everything right.

412
00:32:06,216 --> 00:32:07,593
I think that
maybe the core is poisoned.

413
00:32:07,676 --> 00:32:09,094
Well, if you thought
the core was poisoned,

414
00:32:09,178 --> 00:32:11,722
then you didn't do everything right,
because you're choking my reactor!

415
00:32:11,805 --> 00:32:12,848
Get it back up!

416
00:32:12,932 --> 00:32:15,142
I think if we turn off LAC,

417
00:32:15,225 --> 00:32:17,144
it may be possible
to get more control.

418
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:19,939
-Do it. Go.
-Switch off local automatic control.

419
00:32:20,022 --> 00:32:22,107
Go to global. Leonid.

420
00:32:22,983 --> 00:32:25,402
LAC disabled.
Global control activated.

421
00:32:31,575 --> 00:32:33,035
What did you do?

422
00:32:34,036 --> 00:32:36,664
- I did what you said. I switched...
-DYATLOV: Look at it!

423
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,292
AKIMOV: I don't understand.
DYATLOV: Fucking amateurs.

424
00:32:40,376 --> 00:32:42,211
You've stalled the reactor.

425
00:32:42,294 --> 00:32:44,129
(YELLS) How the fuck
did you get this job?

426
00:32:44,213 --> 00:32:45,297
Comrade Dyatlov...

427
00:32:45,381 --> 00:32:47,007
You're gonna tell me
you did everything right again,

428
00:32:47,091 --> 00:32:48,467
you incompetent asshole?

429
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:51,261
I apologize for this
unsatisfactory result.

430
00:32:57,142 --> 00:32:58,227
What are you doing?

431
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,396
We have to shut all the way down.

432
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:02,940
-No.
-AKIMOV: We could be in a xenon pit.

433
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:04,483
We have to shut down
and wait 24 hours.

434
00:33:04,566 --> 00:33:06,610
No. We're doing the test tonight.
Raise power to 700.

435
00:33:06,694 --> 00:33:08,070
AKIMOV: We can't raise
the power from here.

436
00:33:08,153 --> 00:33:09,738
-The rules...
-Don't talk to me about rules.

437
00:33:09,822 --> 00:33:11,991
-If we fall from 80%...
-No, no. We fell from 50%.

438
00:33:12,074 --> 00:33:14,243
-AKIMOV: 50% is even worse.
-The rules don't say 50.

439
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:15,619
There is no rule!

440
00:33:15,703 --> 00:33:19,581
Comrade Dyatlov, I apologize,
but what you're saying makes no sense.

441
00:33:19,665 --> 00:33:21,583
-Raise the power.
-No.

442
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,795
I won't do it. It isn't safe.

443
00:33:34,138 --> 00:33:36,890
Safety first. Always.

444
00:33:37,766 --> 00:33:40,227
I've been saying that for 25 years.

445
00:33:40,310 --> 00:33:42,312
That's how long
I've done this job, 25 years.

446
00:33:42,396 --> 00:33:43,689
Is that longer than you, Akimov?

447
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:44,857
Yes.

448
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:47,151
-Is it much longer?
-Yes.

449
00:33:47,234 --> 00:33:49,778
And you with your mother's tit
barely out of your mouth?

450
00:33:52,364 --> 00:33:54,533
So if I say it's safe, it's safe.

451
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:55,909
And if the two of you disagree,

452
00:33:55,993 --> 00:33:57,953
then you don't have to work here
and you won't.

453
00:33:58,037 --> 00:33:59,038
But not just here.

454
00:33:59,121 --> 00:34:02,583
You won't work at Kursk or Ignalina
or Leningrad or Novovoronezh.

455
00:34:02,666 --> 00:34:05,711
You won't work anywhere ever again.
I'll see to it.

456
00:34:06,086 --> 00:34:08,505
I think you know I will see to it.

457
00:34:10,174 --> 00:34:11,425
Raise the power.

458
00:34:15,054 --> 00:34:16,764
I would like you
to record your command.

459
00:34:18,057 --> 00:34:19,141
Raise the power.

460
00:34:34,990 --> 00:34:36,200
(BREATHING SHAKILY) Together, then.

461
00:34:39,995 --> 00:34:41,580
DYATLOV: I wasn't even there.

462
00:34:42,372 --> 00:34:43,791
What?

463
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:48,253
I wasn't in the room
when they raised the power.

464
00:34:49,004 --> 00:34:50,464
If you weren't there,
then where were you?

465
00:34:50,547 --> 00:34:53,467
Comrade Legasov,
you are a witness, not a prosecutor.

466
00:34:53,550 --> 00:34:55,385
I will ask the questions here.

467
00:34:56,637 --> 00:34:58,680
If you weren't in the room,
then where were you?

468
00:35:01,391 --> 00:35:02,476
The toilet.

469
00:35:03,393 --> 00:35:05,729
-(INDISTINCT MURMURING)
-STEPASHIN: The toilet?

470
00:35:07,523 --> 00:35:09,316
Comrade Khomyuk interviewed everyone

471
00:35:09,399 --> 00:35:10,818
who was in the control room
that night.

472
00:35:10,901 --> 00:35:12,694
They all told the same story.

473
00:35:16,281 --> 00:35:18,534
"I knew what Dyatlov
ordered was wrong,

474
00:35:18,992 --> 00:35:21,328
"but if I didn't do what he said,
I would be fired."

475
00:35:21,912 --> 00:35:23,413
Leonid Toptunov.

476
00:35:25,082 --> 00:35:26,708
One day before he died.

477
00:35:27,751 --> 00:35:29,628
No, Comrade Dyatlov,
you were in the room.

478
00:35:30,003 --> 00:35:32,464
You ordered them to raise the power.
This is a fact.

479
00:35:33,215 --> 00:35:35,843
(SHCHERBINA COUGHING)

480
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:42,641
(COUGHING CONTINUES)

481
00:35:42,724 --> 00:35:45,435
Court is now in recess.
Thirty minutes.

482
00:35:46,186 --> 00:35:48,021
(COUGHING)

483
00:36:29,354 --> 00:36:32,191
Do you know anything
about this town, Chernobyl?

484
00:36:33,817 --> 00:36:35,235
Not really, no.

485
00:36:36,612 --> 00:36:39,072
It was mostly Jews and Poles.

486
00:36:40,616 --> 00:36:44,286
The Jews were Killed in pogroms,
and Stalin forced the Poles out.

487
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:48,207
And then the Nazis came
and killed whoever was left.

488
00:36:49,291 --> 00:36:50,459
But after the war,

489
00:36:51,919 --> 00:36:53,879
people came to live here anyway.

490
00:36:55,255 --> 00:36:58,842
They knew the ground under
their feet was soaked in blood,

491
00:36:58,926 --> 00:37:00,135
but they didn't care.

492
00:37:01,845 --> 00:37:03,931
Dead Jews, dead Poles.

493
00:37:05,140 --> 00:37:06,183
But not them.

494
00:37:09,853 --> 00:37:12,022
No one ever thinks
it's going to happen to them.

495
00:37:14,191 --> 00:37:15,234
And here we are.

496
00:37:25,202 --> 00:37:26,203
How much time?

497
00:37:27,329 --> 00:37:28,580
Maybe a year.

498
00:37:29,456 --> 00:37:32,251
They call it a... (COUGHS)

499
00:37:32,334 --> 00:37:34,503
They call it a "long illness."

500
00:37:34,586 --> 00:37:36,296
It doesn't seem very long to me.

501
00:37:37,506 --> 00:37:39,591
I know you told me,
and I believed you.

502
00:37:41,093 --> 00:37:42,761
But time passed, and I thought

503
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:45,347
it wouldn't happen to me.

504
00:37:46,473 --> 00:37:47,849
I wasted it.

505
00:37:48,558 --> 00:37:50,644
I wasted it all for nothing.

506
00:37:52,938 --> 00:37:54,189
For nothing?

507
00:37:55,649 --> 00:37:58,443
Do you remember that morning
when I first called you,

508
00:37:58,527 --> 00:38:00,445
how unconcerned I was?

509
00:38:00,529 --> 00:38:02,406
I don't believe much that
comes out of the Kremlin,

510
00:38:02,489 --> 00:38:06,785
but when they told me they were
putting me in charge of the cleanup

511
00:38:07,744 --> 00:38:10,247
and they said it wasn't serious,
I believed them.

512
00:38:12,165 --> 00:38:13,250
You know why?

513
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:16,712
Because they put you in charge.

514
00:38:17,671 --> 00:38:18,714
(SOFTLY) Yeah.

515
00:38:21,842 --> 00:38:24,219
I'm an inconsequential man, Valery.

516
00:38:24,970 --> 00:38:26,680
That's all I've ever been.

517
00:38:28,015 --> 00:38:30,809
I hoped that one day
I would matter, but I didn't.

518
00:38:33,103 --> 00:38:36,023
I just stood next to people who did.

519
00:38:38,525 --> 00:38:40,944
There are other scientists like me.

520
00:38:41,028 --> 00:38:43,405
Any one of them could
have done what I did.

521
00:38:43,488 --> 00:38:44,698
But you...

522
00:38:45,866 --> 00:38:49,619
Everything we asked for,
everything we needed.

523
00:38:51,038 --> 00:38:54,458
Men, material, lunar rovers.

524
00:38:57,294 --> 00:38:59,212
Who else could have done these things?

525
00:39:01,548 --> 00:39:04,092
They heard me,
but they listened to you.

526
00:39:05,302 --> 00:39:08,930
Of all the ministers
and all the deputies,

527
00:39:09,014 --> 00:39:12,642
entire congregation of obedient fools,

528
00:39:13,602 --> 00:39:16,563
they mistakenly sent the one good man.

529
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:19,649
For God's sakes, Boris,

530
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:23,070
you were the one who mattered most.

531
00:39:46,218 --> 00:39:47,886
Ah, it's beautiful.

532
00:40:03,402 --> 00:40:05,612
-(PEOPLE CHATTERING)
-(SIGHS)

533
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:31,763
STEPASHIN: Comrade Legasov.

534
00:40:44,359 --> 00:40:46,403
LEGASOV: The time is 38 past midnight.

535
00:40:47,404 --> 00:40:49,239
The reactor is nearly shut down.

536
00:40:49,906 --> 00:40:51,700
The operators of Reactor 4 are locked

537
00:40:51,783 --> 00:40:53,952
on a path that leads
directly to disaster.

538
00:40:54,536 --> 00:40:56,163
There's no way to turn back.

539
00:40:56,580 --> 00:40:59,040
They do not yet know it,
but the die is cast.

540
00:40:59,875 --> 00:41:03,503
At 30 megawatts,
xenon is still being created,

541
00:41:03,587 --> 00:41:05,338
but none of it is burning away.

542
00:41:07,591 --> 00:41:09,509
The reactor is drowning in poison.

543
00:41:10,260 --> 00:41:13,930
To make matters worse,
the reactor isn't hot enough

544
00:41:14,014 --> 00:41:16,600
to produce sufficient steam.

545
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:21,313
The only way to safely raise
power from this state

546
00:41:21,396 --> 00:41:25,734
is to do it very, very slowly
over the course of 24 hours.

547
00:41:26,526 --> 00:41:28,820
But Dyatlov wants it done now.

548
00:41:29,362 --> 00:41:32,824
Akimov and Toptunov have
only one course of action.

549
00:41:33,742 --> 00:41:36,077
They begin pulling control rods out.

550
00:41:36,745 --> 00:41:37,746
Dozens at a time.

551
00:41:38,246 --> 00:41:40,832
Halfway out,
three-quarters of the way out,

552
00:41:40,916 --> 00:41:43,710
still, the power does not budge.

553
00:41:43,793 --> 00:41:46,505
So they begin pulling
them all the way out.

554
00:41:46,588 --> 00:41:50,383
There were 211 control rods
in Reactor 4.

555
00:41:50,467 --> 00:41:55,138
Akimov and Toptunov
completely withdrew 205.

556
00:41:55,222 --> 00:41:59,226
Remember, control rods
are the brakes on this car.

557
00:41:59,935 --> 00:42:06,441
Of 211 rods, only six
now remain in the reactor.

558
00:42:07,943 --> 00:42:10,737
As for the fuel, it's gone cold,

559
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:12,822
so the negative
temperature coefficient

560
00:42:12,906 --> 00:42:15,492
is no longer
weighing down the reactivity.

561
00:42:15,575 --> 00:42:19,454
But even still,
the xenon poisoning is so strong,

562
00:42:19,538 --> 00:42:23,124
the best they can do is raise
the power to 200 megawatts.

563
00:42:24,543 --> 00:42:26,336
The control rods are out.

564
00:42:26,795 --> 00:42:29,256
The emergency system
has been disconnected.

565
00:42:29,339 --> 00:42:31,508
The only thing keeping
the reactor in check

566
00:42:31,591 --> 00:42:34,177
is water and xenon.

567
00:42:34,261 --> 00:42:38,181
It's 1:00 in the morning.
The test is minutes away.

568
00:43:12,716 --> 00:43:14,843
I'm sorry, this is all we can get.

569
00:43:15,343 --> 00:43:17,762
It's 200 megawatts.
We've pulled almost everything out.

570
00:43:18,346 --> 00:43:19,806
If that's all we have,
that's all we have.

571
00:43:20,265 --> 00:43:23,810
-But the test requires 700.
-Stolyarchuk, let's get ready.

572
00:43:23,893 --> 00:43:25,562
-Switch on pump four.
-AKIMOV: No, wait a second.

573
00:43:25,645 --> 00:43:27,606
-DYATLOV: Stolyarchuk...
-We have barely enough steam as it is.

574
00:43:27,689 --> 00:43:30,108
The turbine is going too slow for
the test to deliver any valid results.

575
00:43:30,191 --> 00:43:31,568
-It's enough.
-And if we add more water,

576
00:43:31,651 --> 00:43:33,320
-there will be even less...
-I said it's enough.

577
00:43:33,403 --> 00:43:34,571
I know what I'm doing. Stolyarchuk.

578
00:43:40,910 --> 00:43:42,287
Main pump four, connected.

579
00:43:42,662 --> 00:43:44,372
We should warn Khodemchuk.
The pipes are gonna be...

580
00:43:44,456 --> 00:43:45,957
Never mind him. Kirschenbaum?

581
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,252
(ALARM SOUNDING)

582
00:43:49,336 --> 00:43:52,047
The steam in the separator drum
is too low, five atmospheres.

583
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:54,841
All right, let's all help him.
Get it up as best you can.

584
00:43:56,885 --> 00:43:59,054
(ALARM CONTINUES)

585
00:43:59,137 --> 00:44:00,221
We should stop.

586
00:44:00,889 --> 00:44:02,557
DYATLOV: Turn that fucking thing off.

587
00:44:03,725 --> 00:44:05,352
You have 15 minutes.

588
00:44:07,228 --> 00:44:08,396
<i>LEGASOV: Fifteen minutes.</i>

589
00:44:09,648 --> 00:44:12,067
They may as well have had 15 days.

590
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:15,153
The problem they were facing
was not solvable.

591
00:44:15,236 --> 00:44:17,864
The power was too low.
The water was too high.

592
00:44:17,947 --> 00:44:19,574
The test was already ruined.

593
00:44:19,658 --> 00:44:22,619
The results would have been useless,
but Dyatlov didn't care.

594
00:44:23,036 --> 00:44:25,747
All he wanted to do was
report a completed test.

595
00:44:27,207 --> 00:44:29,334
1:22 a.m.

596
00:44:30,043 --> 00:44:31,920
Less than two minutes remain.

597
00:44:33,171 --> 00:44:37,133
Yuvchenko, a mechanical engineer,
is in his office.

598
00:44:41,346 --> 00:44:43,723
Perevozchenko,
reactor section foreman,

599
00:44:43,807 --> 00:44:44,974
is in the refueling hall,

600
00:44:45,558 --> 00:44:49,145
high above the 1,000-ton
steel reactor cover.

601
00:44:50,230 --> 00:44:51,481
(RUMBLING)

602
00:44:51,564 --> 00:44:53,566
Degtaryenko, Khodemchuk,

603
00:44:53,650 --> 00:44:56,444
circulation operators,
are in the pump room.

604
00:44:58,697 --> 00:45:01,950
None of them
have been told about the test.

605
00:45:02,033 --> 00:45:03,868
None of them know
what is about to happen.

606
00:45:04,661 --> 00:45:09,708
At 1:22 and 30 seconds,
Toptunov sees a report

607
00:45:10,583 --> 00:45:13,420
from the reactor's
SKALA computer system.

608
00:45:14,629 --> 00:45:17,966
Based on the absence
of sufficient control rods,

609
00:45:18,049 --> 00:45:21,219
the computer is recommending
that the reactor be shut down.

610
00:45:27,142 --> 00:45:29,602
Well, of course it's saying that.
It doesn't know we're running a test.

611
00:45:31,771 --> 00:45:32,856
All right, comrades.

612
00:45:34,691 --> 00:45:37,193
Another few minutes,
it will all be over.

613
00:45:37,277 --> 00:45:38,653
Kirschenbaum, when you're ready.

614
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:41,072
We did everything right.

615
00:45:43,575 --> 00:45:45,076
KIRSCHENBAUM: Oscillograph on.

616
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:48,788
Closing number eight throttle valve.

617
00:45:49,914 --> 00:45:51,458
STOLYARCHUK: Generator rotor
beginning rundown.

618
00:45:51,916 --> 00:45:54,627
LEGASOV: 71:23 and four seconds.

619
00:45:55,462 --> 00:45:59,340
With every decision, they have pulled
this reactor back like a slingshot,

620
00:45:59,424 --> 00:46:01,468
further than anyone has ever pulled.

621
00:46:02,051 --> 00:46:03,636
Now the test begins.

622
00:46:04,179 --> 00:46:07,140
The pumps are shut down,
and they've let go.

623
00:46:10,268 --> 00:46:13,021
The pumps stop moving water
through the reactor.

624
00:46:13,688 --> 00:46:16,775
Uranium fuel is now
unchecked by fresh coolant,

625
00:46:16,858 --> 00:46:18,818
unchecked by control rods.

626
00:46:18,902 --> 00:46:21,905
The balance immediately swings
in the opposite direction.

627
00:46:21,988 --> 00:46:25,116
In less than a second,
reactivity increases.

628
00:46:26,451 --> 00:46:27,869
Inside the core,

629
00:46:27,952 --> 00:46:30,288
the remaining water is
quickly converting to steam.

630
00:46:30,371 --> 00:46:32,540
A void is being created.

631
00:46:32,624 --> 00:46:35,168
There is no fresh water to replace it.

632
00:46:35,251 --> 00:46:38,171
Steam increases reactivity,

633
00:46:38,254 --> 00:46:41,549
increases heat, increases steam,

634
00:46:41,633 --> 00:46:43,259
increases reactivity.

635
00:46:44,552 --> 00:46:47,597
The remaining xenon decays away.

636
00:46:49,015 --> 00:46:50,517
The power is rising.

637
00:46:52,811 --> 00:46:54,312
There's nothing left to stop it.

638
00:46:55,688 --> 00:46:59,108
1:23 and 35 seconds.

639
00:47:02,445 --> 00:47:04,531
We have a power surge! Sasha!

640
00:47:10,036 --> 00:47:11,162
(SHOUTS) What did you do?

641
00:47:11,746 --> 00:47:14,958
1:23 and 40 seconds.

642
00:47:23,174 --> 00:47:25,677
In every control room
of every nuclear reactor in the world,

643
00:47:25,760 --> 00:47:28,930
there is a button
with one single purpose,

644
00:47:29,013 --> 00:47:32,433
to "scram," or instantly
shut down the reaction.

645
00:47:32,517 --> 00:47:35,770
In Soviet reactors,
that button is called AZ-5.

646
00:47:36,688 --> 00:47:38,731
You press AZ-5,

647
00:47:38,815 --> 00:47:41,025
all of the control rods
insert at once,

648
00:47:41,109 --> 00:47:44,654
and the reaction is stopped dead.

649
00:47:45,738 --> 00:47:46,906
But...

650
00:47:48,575 --> 00:47:50,159
(SIGHS)

651
00:47:53,454 --> 00:47:54,747
What are you waiting for, Legasov?

652
00:47:54,831 --> 00:47:56,749
-(KNOCK ON TABLE)
-Tell your lies.

653
00:47:56,833 --> 00:47:59,043
KADNIKOV: Comrade Dyatlov,
you will not be warned again.

654
00:47:59,127 --> 00:48:01,337
-DYATLOV: Or what?
-For God's sake, Dyatlov.

655
00:48:01,421 --> 00:48:03,423
-Legasov's already given it away.
-That's enough.

656
00:48:03,506 --> 00:48:06,551
He said before there was no way
to avoid what was coming.

657
00:48:06,634 --> 00:48:08,261
-He knows something.
-Comrade Dyatlov.

658
00:48:08,344 --> 00:48:09,929
She knows something.

659
00:48:10,013 --> 00:48:11,139
(GRAVEL POUNDING)

660
00:48:11,222 --> 00:48:13,266
DYATLOV: I know what you are,
Valery Alexeyevich.

661
00:48:13,349 --> 00:48:16,352
-You're a liar.
-We've heard enough for today.

662
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:20,231
The defendants will be
remanded in custody.

663
00:48:20,315 --> 00:48:23,318
-Court will...
-I haven't finished.

664
00:48:23,401 --> 00:48:25,528
I still have more evidence to give.

665
00:48:25,612 --> 00:48:28,907
It's not necessary.
Your testimony is concluded.

666
00:48:28,990 --> 00:48:32,160
-Your Honor.
-Court is now adjourned.

667
00:48:32,243 --> 00:48:34,454
-We will resume tomorrow with...
-SHCHERBINA: Let him finish.

668
00:48:37,165 --> 00:48:38,499
KADNIKOV: Comrade Shcherbina...

669
00:48:41,252 --> 00:48:42,295
Let him finish.

670
00:49:07,570 --> 00:49:09,906
Dyatlov broke every rule we have.

671
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:12,116
(SIGHS)

672
00:49:13,618 --> 00:49:16,746
He pushed a reactor
to the brink of destruction.

673
00:49:17,914 --> 00:49:19,248
(SIGHS)

674
00:49:21,292 --> 00:49:23,878
He did these things believing
there was a failsafe.

675
00:49:23,962 --> 00:49:27,423
AZ-5, a simple button
to shut it all down.

676
00:49:27,507 --> 00:49:32,053
But in the circumstances he created,
there wasn't.

677
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:35,348
The shutdown system had a fatal flaw.

678
00:49:37,475 --> 00:49:42,730
At 1:23:40, Akimov engages AZ-5.

679
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:47,402
(ALARM BUZZES)

680
00:49:50,780 --> 00:49:54,575
The fully withdrawn control rods
begin moving back into the reactor.

681
00:49:54,659 --> 00:49:57,328
These rods are made of boron,
which reduces reactivity,

682
00:49:57,412 --> 00:49:58,496
but not their tips.

683
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:03,626
The tips are made of graphite,
which accelerates reactivity.

684
00:50:04,127 --> 00:50:05,128
KADNIKOV: Why?

685
00:50:09,799 --> 00:50:10,925
LEGASOV: Why?

686
00:50:13,553 --> 00:50:15,847
For the same reason our reactors

687
00:50:15,930 --> 00:50:18,016
do not have containment
buildings around them,

688
00:50:18,975 --> 00:50:20,101
like those in the West.

689
00:50:20,184 --> 00:50:24,897
For the same reason we don't use
properly enriched fuel in our cores.

690
00:50:25,148 --> 00:50:27,483
For the same reason
we are the only nation

691
00:50:27,567 --> 00:50:31,904
that builds water-cooled,
graphite-moderated reactors

692
00:50:31,988 --> 00:50:34,449
with a positive void coefficient.

693
00:50:36,325 --> 00:50:37,368
It's cheaper.

694
00:50:37,452 --> 00:50:40,663
(CROWD MURMURING)

695
00:50:43,583 --> 00:50:44,834
LEGASOV: (CLEARS THROAT)
The first part

696
00:50:44,917 --> 00:50:46,711
of the rods that enter the core

697
00:50:46,794 --> 00:50:48,129
are the graphite tips.

698
00:50:48,212 --> 00:50:50,548
And when they do,
the reaction in the core,

699
00:50:50,631 --> 00:50:53,509
which had been rising, skyrockets.

700
00:50:53,593 --> 00:50:58,598
Every last molecule of liquid water
instantly converts to steam,

701
00:50:58,681 --> 00:51:01,976
which expands and ruptures
a series of fuel rod channels.

702
00:51:02,060 --> 00:51:06,147
The control rods in those
channels can move no further.

703
00:51:06,230 --> 00:51:08,691
The graphite tips
are fixed in position,

704
00:51:08,775 --> 00:51:11,652
endlessly accelerating the reaction.

705
00:51:11,736 --> 00:51:15,573
Chernobyl Reactor 4
IS NOW a nuclear bomb.

706
00:51:16,115 --> 00:51:18,659
-(LOUD RUMBLING)
-LEGASOV: 7:23:42.

707
00:51:18,743 --> 00:51:22,705
Perevozchenko looks down on
the enormous steel lid of the reactor

708
00:51:22,789 --> 00:51:24,791
and sees the impossible.

709
00:51:24,874 --> 00:51:26,667
The control rod and fuel channel caps,

710
00:51:26,751 --> 00:51:28,836
which each weigh 350 kilograms,

711
00:51:28,920 --> 00:51:30,588
are jumping up and down.

712
00:51:31,130 --> 00:51:33,341
He runs to warn the control room.

713
00:51:33,424 --> 00:51:36,344
But there's nothing he can do
to stop what is coming.

714
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:39,430
-(ALARM BUZZING)
-1:23 and 44 seconds.

715
00:51:40,056 --> 00:51:43,476
The steam blows
more fuel channels apart.

716
00:51:43,559 --> 00:51:45,603
We do not know
how high the power went.

717
00:51:45,686 --> 00:51:46,896
We only know the final reading.

718
00:51:46,979 --> 00:51:49,398
(ALARM CONTINUES)

719
00:51:49,482 --> 00:51:54,028
Reactor 4, designed to operate
at 3,200 megawatts,

720
00:51:54,779 --> 00:51:57,323
went beyond 33,000.

721
00:52:03,079 --> 00:52:06,874
The pressure inside the core
can no longer be held back.

722
00:52:06,958 --> 00:52:13,256
At long last, we have arrived.
1:23:45, explosion.

723
00:52:13,339 --> 00:52:14,799
(EXPLOSION)

724
00:52:14,882 --> 00:52:17,844
In the instant the lid is
thrown off the reactor,

725
00:52:17,927 --> 00:52:18,970
oxygen rushes in.

726
00:52:19,053 --> 00:52:23,141
It combines with hydrogen
and super-heated graphite.

727
00:52:25,184 --> 00:52:28,020
The chain of disaster is now complete.

728
00:52:50,168 --> 00:52:51,586
AKIMOV: (MUFFLED) Comrade Dyatlov!

729
00:52:56,841 --> 00:52:58,176
Comrade Dyatlov!

730
00:53:04,223 --> 00:53:06,309
(INAUDIBLE)

731
00:53:09,687 --> 00:53:12,565
LEGASOV: No one in the room
that night knew

732
00:53:12,648 --> 00:53:15,818
the shutdown button
could act as a detonator.

733
00:53:17,445 --> 00:53:18,779
They didn't know I,

734
00:53:20,448 --> 00:53:22,450
because it was kept from them.

735
00:53:22,533 --> 00:53:27,288
Comrade Legasov, you're contradicting
your own testimony in Vienna.

736
00:53:27,705 --> 00:53:29,665
My testimony in Vienna was a lie.

737
00:53:29,749 --> 00:53:31,083
(CROWD MURMURING)

738
00:53:31,167 --> 00:53:33,461
LEGASOV: I lied to the world.

739
00:53:34,295 --> 00:53:36,130
I'm not the only one
who kept this secret.

740
00:53:36,214 --> 00:53:37,215
There are many.

741
00:53:38,799 --> 00:53:40,218
We were following orders,

742
00:53:41,802 --> 00:53:43,429
from the KGB,
from the Central Committee.

743
00:53:43,512 --> 00:53:46,057
And right now, there are
16 reactors in the Soviet Union

744
00:53:46,140 --> 00:53:48,601
with the same fatal flaw.

745
00:53:48,684 --> 00:53:50,561
Three of them are still running

746
00:53:50,645 --> 00:53:53,064
less than 20 kilometers away
at Chernobyl.

747
00:53:53,147 --> 00:53:57,068
Professor Legasov, if you mean
to suggest the Soviet state

748
00:53:57,151 --> 00:53:58,986
is somehow responsible
for what happened,

749
00:53:59,070 --> 00:54:01,781
then I must warn you, you are
treading on dangerous ground.

750
00:54:02,490 --> 00:54:04,158
I've already trod on dangerous ground.

751
00:54:04,242 --> 00:54:06,285
We're on dangerous ground right now,

752
00:54:06,369 --> 00:54:09,121
because of our secrets and our lies.

753
00:54:09,205 --> 00:54:12,250
They're practically what define us.

754
00:54:12,333 --> 00:54:15,544
When the truth offends, we lie and lie

755
00:54:15,628 --> 00:54:17,880
until we can no longer
remember it is even there.

756
00:54:17,964 --> 00:54:19,548
But it is still there.

757
00:54:23,219 --> 00:54:27,265
Every lie we tell incurs
a debt to the truth.

758
00:54:29,642 --> 00:54:31,811
Sooner or later, that debt is paid.

759
00:54:36,732 --> 00:54:41,654
That is how an RBMK
reactor core explodes.

760
00:54:45,700 --> 00:54:46,701
Lies.

761
00:56:51,367 --> 00:56:53,661
Valery Alexeyevich Legasov,

762
00:56:55,246 --> 00:56:57,456
son of Alexei Legasov,

763
00:56:57,665 --> 00:57:00,126
Head of ideological Compliance,
Central Committee.

764
00:57:01,168 --> 00:57:02,670
Do you know
what your father did there?

765
00:57:03,003 --> 00:57:04,004
Yes.

766
00:57:05,381 --> 00:57:08,717
As a student, you had a
leadership position in Komsomol.

767
00:57:08,801 --> 00:57:10,845
Communist Youth, correct?

768
00:57:12,221 --> 00:57:14,140
-You already know.
-Answer the question.

769
00:57:14,557 --> 00:57:15,599
Yes.

770
00:57:17,601 --> 00:57:19,603
At the Kurchatov Institute,

771
00:57:19,687 --> 00:57:21,856
you were the
Communist Party secretary.

772
00:57:22,565 --> 00:57:26,235
In the position, you limited
the promotion of Jewish scientists.

773
00:57:31,198 --> 00:57:32,783
Yes.

774
00:57:32,867 --> 00:57:35,494
To curry favor with Kremlin officials.

775
00:57:41,125 --> 00:57:43,002
You're one of us, Legasov.

776
00:57:44,837 --> 00:57:46,714
I can do anything I want with you.

777
00:57:48,466 --> 00:57:51,343
But what I want the most is
for you to know that I know.

778
00:57:52,636 --> 00:57:54,138
You're not brave.

779
00:57:55,681 --> 00:57:57,141
You're not heroic.

780
00:57:58,809 --> 00:58:02,188
You're just a dying man
who forgot himself.

781
00:58:02,271 --> 00:58:05,733
I know who I am,
and I know what I've done.

782
00:58:08,527 --> 00:58:10,905
In a just world,
I'd be shot for my lies,

783
00:58:10,988 --> 00:58:13,199
but not for this, not for the truth.

784
00:58:14,158 --> 00:58:16,327
Scientists,

785
00:58:16,410 --> 00:58:20,122
and your idiot obsession
with reasons.

786
00:58:20,206 --> 00:58:24,627
(YELLS) When the bullet hits
your skull, what will it matter why?

787
00:58:32,301 --> 00:58:34,637
No one's getting shot, Legasov.

788
00:58:36,347 --> 00:58:38,015
The whole world saw you in Vienna.

789
00:58:38,849 --> 00:58:40,935
It would be embarrassing
to kill you now.

790
00:58:41,018 --> 00:58:42,061
And for what?

791
00:58:43,437 --> 00:58:46,482
Your testimony today
will not be accepted by the State.

792
00:58:46,565 --> 00:58:48,901
It will not be disseminated
in the press.

793
00:58:49,568 --> 00:58:51,403
It never happened.

794
00:58:52,780 --> 00:58:57,034
No, you will live,
however long you have,

795
00:58:57,826 --> 00:59:00,579
but not as a scientist, not anymore.

796
00:59:01,580 --> 00:59:05,543
You'll keep your title
and your office,

797
00:59:06,752 --> 00:59:11,090
but no duties,
no authority, no friends.

798
00:59:11,173 --> 00:59:12,508
No one will talk to you.

799
00:59:13,342 --> 00:59:14,718
No one will listen to you.

800
00:59:17,179 --> 00:59:20,599
Other men, lesser men,

801
00:59:21,725 --> 00:59:24,436
will receive credit
for the things you have done.

802
00:59:25,396 --> 00:59:27,690
Your legacy is now their legacy.

803
00:59:27,773 --> 00:59:29,984
You'll live long enough to see that.

804
00:59:33,946 --> 00:59:35,781
What role did Shcherbina play in this?

805
00:59:36,532 --> 00:59:37,616
None.

806
00:59:37,700 --> 00:59:39,535
He didn't know what I was gonna say.

807
00:59:41,453 --> 00:59:43,539
What role did Khomyuk play in this?

808
00:59:44,206 --> 00:59:45,207
None.

809
00:59:46,083 --> 00:59:47,501
She didn't know either.

810
00:59:50,045 --> 00:59:52,506
After all you've said and done today,

811
00:59:52,590 --> 00:59:58,220
it would be curious
if you chose this moment to lie.

812
01:00:01,432 --> 01:00:05,436
I would think a man of your experience
would know a lie when he hears one.

813
01:00:09,773 --> 01:00:12,776
You will not meet or communicate
with either one of them ever again.

814
01:00:14,278 --> 01:00:17,740
You will not communicate with anyone
about Chernobyl ever again.

815
01:00:19,241 --> 01:00:21,493
You will remain so immaterial
to the world around you

816
01:00:21,577 --> 01:00:23,454
that when you finally do die,

817
01:00:24,079 --> 01:00:27,666
it will be exceedingly hard
to know that you ever lived at all.

818
01:00:32,129 --> 01:00:33,839
And if I refuse?

819
01:00:37,217 --> 01:00:40,137
Why worry about something
that isn't going to happen?

820
01:00:40,220 --> 01:00:41,472
(CHUCKLES)

821
01:00:41,555 --> 01:00:44,767
"Why worry about something
that isn't going to happen?"

822
01:00:45,726 --> 01:00:47,269
Oh, that's perfect.

823
01:00:48,145 --> 01:00:49,980
They should put that on our money.

824
01:01:21,053 --> 01:01:23,430
(ENGINE STARTS)

825
01:02:00,426 --> 01:02:03,178
LEGASOV: (ON TAPE)
To be a scientist is to be naive.

826
01:02:04,513 --> 01:02:06,849
We are so focused
on our search for truth,

827
01:02:06,932 --> 01:02:11,103
we fail to consider how few
actually want us to find it.

828
01:02:11,645 --> 01:02:15,858
But it is always there,
whether we see it or not,

829
01:02:15,941 --> 01:02:17,901
whether we choose to or not.

830
01:02:17,985 --> 01:02:20,696
The truth doesn't care
about our needs or wants.

831
01:02:20,779 --> 01:02:22,448
It doesn't care about our governments,

832
01:02:22,531 --> 01:02:24,867
our ideologies, our religions.

833
01:02:26,326 --> 01:02:28,787
It will lie in wait for all time.

834
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:34,001
And this, at last,
is the gift of Chernobyl.

835
01:02:34,084 --> 01:02:36,545
Where I once would fear
the cost of truth,

836
01:02:36,628 --> 01:02:38,255
now I only ask,

837
01:02:40,424 --> 01:02:42,384
"What is the cost of lies?”

838
01:02:48,015 --> 01:02:51,310
(SOMBER INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

